1
00:01:07,600 --> 00:01:09,960
[Episode 16:
A Two-Day, One-Night Luxury Hotel Trip For Two]

2
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:24,993
Ren Xi Zhou!

3
00:01:28,120 --> 00:01:29,620
Look up.

4
00:01:45,280 --> 00:01:47,028
Can I hold your hand?

5
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:09,520
Why so close? You have a crush on me?

6
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:11,960
I need to keep 25 cm away from him.

7
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:13,577
20 cm is also fine.

8
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:19,843
Thank you, Mr. Xiang.

9
00:03:19,843 --> 00:03:21,177
Sorry for the bother.

10
00:03:21,919 --> 00:03:24,960
Oh, right, who got first place?

11
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:26,159
Auntie Qiu's son.

12
00:03:26,159 --> 00:03:27,840
He sang "Hou Yi" in opera style.

13
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:30,280
Way better than us, you know.

14
00:03:30,280 --> 00:03:32,560
He sang "My Sun".

15
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:34,800
It's no big deal.

16
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:36,885
We got second place anyway.

17
00:03:38,040 --> 00:03:39,879
Only two acts were competing.

18
00:03:39,879 --> 00:03:43,239
The rest were performed by the arts troupe.

19
00:03:48,280 --> 00:03:50,229
A two-day, one-night luxury hotel trip for two.

20
00:03:50,229 --> 00:03:51,712
Who's going?

21
00:03:52,719 --> 00:03:55,479
Forget it. They check IDs at the hotel.

22
00:03:55,479 --> 00:03:58,587
My dad would definitely track me down.

23
00:03:59,745 --> 00:04:01,320
You go.

24
00:04:01,320 --> 00:04:04,046
What a pity. I'm booked for an audition.

25
00:04:12,599 --> 00:04:13,976
<i>Hold on.</i>

26
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:18,480
<i>Luxury double room?</i>

27
00:04:18,480 --> 00:04:22,708
<i>No way. This can't be real!</i>

28
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:38,437
That's it.

29
00:04:38,437 --> 00:04:40,240
I want to use the free stay.

30
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:42,906
Need you to cover for me at my mom's place.

31
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:46,901
But I've been getting a lot of orders.

32
00:04:50,760 --> 00:04:52,240
Is this a goldfish?

33
00:04:52,240 --> 00:04:54,120
That's a sea goldfish.

34
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:55,760
It's very timid.

35
00:04:55,760 --> 00:04:59,175
So I got a tank big enough for a rock.

36
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:01,920
Where were we?

37
00:05:01,920 --> 00:05:04,085
I want to use the free stay.

38
00:05:04,840 --> 00:05:07,279
You must be sick of hotels already, huh?

39
00:05:07,279 --> 00:05:09,680
The feeling of using your own money

40
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:11,040
is nothing like using your dad's, right?

41
00:05:11,040 --> 00:05:14,639
I'm happier when using the money I earned.

42
00:05:14,639 --> 00:05:16,279
I'm also happier

43
00:05:16,279 --> 00:05:19,320
using a coupon I won than paying for a stay.

44
00:05:19,320 --> 00:05:20,760
That's it, really.

45
00:05:20,760 --> 00:05:22,279
Don't get the wrong idea.

46
00:05:22,279 --> 00:05:23,959
Plus, I'll make it worth your while.

47
00:05:23,959 --> 00:05:26,540
I'll pay you at the busy-season hourly rate.

48
00:05:27,840 --> 00:05:29,960
I'll think about it.

49
00:05:29,960 --> 00:05:32,439
But aren't you going to prepare?

50
00:05:32,439 --> 00:05:34,240
Prepare for what?

51
00:05:34,240 --> 00:05:35,960
Weren't they just fighting the other day?

52
00:05:35,960 --> 00:05:38,854
Why the sudden overnight plan for tomorrow?

53
00:05:38,854 --> 00:05:40,160
It's for work.

54
00:05:40,160 --> 00:05:41,720
They're going on a business trip.

55
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:43,660
The company booked the wrong room,
so they'll have to...

56
00:05:43,660 --> 00:05:47,320
- Spend the night together.
- It's just sharing a space temporarily

57
00:05:47,320 --> 00:05:51,360
until morning,
while keeping at least 20 cm apart.

58
00:05:51,360 --> 00:05:52,680
They're sleeping together.

59
00:05:52,680 --> 00:05:54,000
It's just sharing a space--

60
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:55,399
Anyway,

61
00:05:55,399 --> 00:05:58,000
your friend is going to be alone
with his ex on a work trip,

62
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:00,359
and you're here to get our take on it, right?

63
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:02,360
Foundation cream,

64
00:06:02,360 --> 00:06:04,983
hair wax, a razor, all essentials.

65
00:06:05,640 --> 00:06:08,239
I went to get everything ready after your call.

66
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:20,920
It's getting late.

67
00:06:20,920 --> 00:06:22,030
I have to go.

68
00:06:22,030 --> 00:06:23,544
My treat today.

69
00:06:28,840 --> 00:06:30,590
Wait for me.

70
00:06:37,639 --> 00:06:38,720
Not bad.

71
00:06:38,720 --> 00:06:41,112
Similar to other hotels I've stayed in.

72
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:51,160
I'm going to see
if they can give us a standard room.

73
00:06:51,160 --> 00:06:53,480
I already called before coming.

74
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:55,680
They told me they're fully booked.

75
00:06:55,680 --> 00:06:57,441
Probably because it's peak season.

76
00:07:01,480 --> 00:07:03,639
There's a desk over there

77
00:07:03,639 --> 00:07:06,160
if you need to work.

78
00:07:06,160 --> 00:07:08,120
The first draft is already done.

79
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:10,040
I'm waiting for the producer's feedback.

80
00:07:10,040 --> 00:07:12,360
So no work for now.

81
00:07:12,360 --> 00:07:15,040
That was so fast.

82
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:16,800
I didn't mean to rush it.

83
00:07:16,800 --> 00:07:19,057
My editor kept pushing me.

84
00:07:19,720 --> 00:07:20,840
<i>Mr. Xiang.</i>

85
00:07:20,840 --> 00:07:22,199
<i>You can take your time with this.</i>

86
00:07:22,199 --> 00:07:24,800
<i>Actually, this project isn't that urgent.</i>

87
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:26,120
Is the writing not as good now?

88
00:07:26,120 --> 00:07:27,617
<i>No, not at all.</i>

89
00:07:27,617 --> 00:07:30,600
<i>The recent scripts have been great.</i>

90
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:31,639
<i>It's just...</i>

91
00:07:31,639 --> 00:07:34,218
You can talk to me if there are any problems.

92
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:36,800
<i>It's just that you write too fast.</i>

93
00:07:36,800 --> 00:07:38,920
<i>The producer is still
working on other projects.</i>

94
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:40,560
<i>He can't give you feedback in time.</i>

95
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:42,087
<i>Is that okay with you?</i>

96
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:44,680
It's fine. I'll continue at my pace.

97
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:47,120
You guys just follow your own schedule.

98
00:07:47,120 --> 00:07:49,360
<i>Now I see why you're a top scriptwriter.</i>

99
00:07:49,360 --> 00:07:51,560
<i>You're literally the model worker.</i>

100
00:07:51,560 --> 00:07:54,048
<i>Is your health holding up?</i>

101
00:08:02,840 --> 00:08:04,607
I'm perfectly fine.

102
00:08:04,607 --> 00:08:07,200
But your eye bags...

103
00:08:07,200 --> 00:08:08,599
Occupational hazard.

104
00:08:14,480 --> 00:08:16,440
Will coming out here with me

105
00:08:16,440 --> 00:08:18,510
interfere with your work?

106
00:08:19,480 --> 00:08:21,600
My mom's sick of me.

107
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:25,040
She'd love for me
to be out of her hair for a few days.

108
00:08:25,040 --> 00:08:27,125
Come on, sit down, please.

109
00:08:30,240 --> 00:08:32,120
Just tell me what you need.

110
00:08:32,120 --> 00:08:33,840
It's not a big deal.

111
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:35,755
I just want to ask for a few days off.

112
00:08:35,755 --> 00:08:37,640
My friend will cover for me,

113
00:08:37,640 --> 00:08:40,285
and I'll pay her myself.

114
00:08:41,560 --> 00:08:43,358
What's the leave for?

115
00:08:49,120 --> 00:08:50,795
Good like this?

116
00:08:51,480 --> 00:08:52,480
Go harder.

117
00:08:52,480 --> 00:08:53,984
Okay.

118
00:09:00,040 --> 00:09:01,360
It's something
played on a flat surface like a table,

119
00:09:01,360 --> 00:09:03,639
and they revolve around certain rules--

120
00:09:03,639 --> 00:09:04,960
Board games.

121
00:09:04,960 --> 00:09:06,158
Yeah, right.

122
00:09:06,840 --> 00:09:08,394
Which one do you want to play?

123
00:09:13,040 --> 00:09:15,595
<i>He was worried
that we'd be embarrassed being alone,</i>

124
00:09:15,595 --> 00:09:17,168
<i>so...</i>

125
00:09:17,880 --> 00:09:19,488
Did you go shopping for these?

126
00:09:20,920 --> 00:09:22,742
Zhu Qiao Fei forgot these at my home.

127
00:09:23,560 --> 00:09:25,886
He said it's fine to use them.

128
00:09:29,800 --> 00:09:31,039
This is Monopoly.

129
00:09:31,039 --> 00:09:32,080
This is Settlers of Catan.

130
00:09:32,080 --> 00:09:33,958
And this is Splendor.

131
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:36,440
Why did you...

132
00:09:36,440 --> 00:09:37,679
If there's nothing to say,

133
00:09:37,679 --> 00:09:39,986
just play games with her.

134
00:09:41,800 --> 00:09:42,840
Got it.

135
00:09:42,840 --> 00:09:44,482
I'll pass these on to him.

136
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:52,300
So he's really into that girl, right?

137
00:09:54,919 --> 00:09:56,200
Why does a moon halo

138
00:09:56,200 --> 00:09:58,080
mean sunshine the next day?

139
00:09:58,760 --> 00:10:01,680
There's a saying
that wind follows the moon halo.

140
00:10:01,680 --> 00:10:02,960
A moon halo actually means

141
00:10:02,960 --> 00:10:05,500
wind or rain is coming.

142
00:10:06,160 --> 00:10:08,840
I was wrong back then.

143
00:10:08,840 --> 00:10:10,330
Oh, I see.

144
00:10:11,960 --> 00:10:13,934
If only I'd known the truth earlier.

145
00:10:14,720 --> 00:10:16,840
That way

146
00:10:16,840 --> 00:10:18,919
I wouldn't have gotten caught in the rain

147
00:10:18,919 --> 00:10:21,320
every time I saw a moon halo.

148
00:10:24,240 --> 00:10:26,232
Do you still like Ren Xi Zhou?

149
00:10:31,759 --> 00:10:32,840
You know that.

150
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:34,696
I'm that friend.

151
00:10:36,760 --> 00:10:38,559
I was planning to play dumb.

152
00:10:38,559 --> 00:10:40,840
Guess my acting skills need work.

153
00:10:40,840 --> 00:10:42,120
Actually,

154
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:43,880
the typical thing to say is,

155
00:10:43,880 --> 00:10:47,310
"She's mine. Stay away from her."

156
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:50,703
She's free.

157
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:53,884
You're right.

158
00:10:55,679 --> 00:10:57,280
What's with that look?

159
00:10:57,280 --> 00:10:59,400
It's all in the past.

160
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:01,159
Back when I was 17 or 18,

161
00:11:01,159 --> 00:11:02,520
I couldn't figure out

162
00:11:02,520 --> 00:11:04,280
why I lost.

163
00:11:04,280 --> 00:11:06,147
But now I get it.

164
00:11:08,240 --> 00:11:10,145
Actually, fortune's on your side.

165
00:11:10,145 --> 00:11:11,422
Look,

166
00:11:11,422 --> 00:11:13,663
tomorrow will be sunny.

167
00:11:17,520 --> 00:11:18,929
I win!

168
00:11:21,679 --> 00:11:23,000
Time to sleep.

169
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:25,607
You said you wanted to go sightseeing tomorrow.

170
00:11:34,720 --> 00:11:36,350
20 cm, I know.

171
00:11:38,440 --> 00:11:40,380
Go get ready for the bath.

172
00:11:42,140 --> 00:11:43,863
I'll start the water for you.

173
00:12:33,799 --> 00:12:36,320
The friend you mentioned

174
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:38,960
is actually you, right?

175
00:12:38,960 --> 00:12:41,107
How's that possible?

176
00:12:43,760 --> 00:12:45,800
Keep it to yourself.

177
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:48,412
I'll definitely help you with this.

178
00:12:48,412 --> 00:12:49,439
Thank you.

179
00:12:49,439 --> 00:12:51,080
So you two got together and then broke up.

180
00:12:51,080 --> 00:12:53,080
When did that start? What went wrong?

181
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:54,920
Why keep it from us?

182
00:12:54,920 --> 00:12:57,279
It's a long story.

183
00:12:57,279 --> 00:12:59,720
Actually, we met a long time ago.

184
00:12:59,720 --> 00:13:01,680
When I was eight...

185
00:13:01,680 --> 00:13:04,435
Let's talk about something I'm interested in.

186
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:10,207
Are you ready for that?

187
00:13:10,207 --> 00:13:11,480
<i>Come on.</i>

188
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:13,308
<i>He wouldn't dare.</i>

189
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:16,407
<i>But...</i>

190
00:13:17,159 --> 00:13:18,480
<i>just in case.</i>

191
00:13:18,480 --> 00:13:20,462
<i>What exactly is our relationship now?</i>

192
00:13:21,159 --> 00:13:22,278
<i>Whatever,</i>

193
00:13:22,278 --> 00:13:24,226
<i>it's a new era.</i>

194
00:13:32,240 --> 00:13:33,876
Still working out?

195
00:13:37,360 --> 00:13:40,112
Health is something we writers can't ignore.

196
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:45,880
I'm done.

197
00:13:45,880 --> 00:13:47,621
I'll go get cleaned up then.

198
00:13:51,720 --> 00:13:53,279
I spent a lot on this sleepwear.

199
00:13:53,279 --> 00:13:55,094
It can't be for nothing.

200
00:13:55,772 --> 00:13:56,960
Please.

201
00:13:56,960 --> 00:13:59,472
Don't let my money go to waste.
